WEBVTT

00:01.068 --> 00:03.002
Dre:<i> As a father,</i>

00:03.004 --> 00:04.136
<i>there's nothing better than</i>
<i>the birth of your first son.</i>

00:04.138 --> 00:05.437
<i>Your son is the person</i>

00:05.439 --> 00:07.439
<i>who is supposed to carry on</i>
<i>your legacy,</i>

00:07.441 --> 00:08.774
<i>your flyness,</i>

00:08.776 --> 00:11.310
<i>someone you hope</i>
<i>will be just like you.</i>

00:11.312 --> 00:13.112
<i>So it's a real kick</i>
<i>in the berries</i>

00:13.114 --> 00:16.949
<i>when you find out your son</i>
<i>isn't a damn thing like you.</i>

00:16.951 --> 00:18.283
I'm gonna go try on my tights.

00:18.285 --> 00:19.818
<i>It's even worse</i>
<i>when you find out</i>

00:19.820 --> 00:22.021
<i>not only is he not like you...</i>

00:22.023 --> 00:23.555
<i>He's not like anybody.</i>

00:23.557 --> 00:25.557
I want to have
a Bar Mitzvah.
A...?

00:25.559 --> 00:27.993
I'm gonna go with either
Schlomo or Schmuel.
What?

00:27.995 --> 00:29.328
You get to be my best man.

00:29.330 --> 00:30.329
Ohh!

00:30.331 --> 00:32.064
Bachelor party
at Medieval Times!

00:32.066 --> 00:33.399
Ahh.

00:33.401 --> 00:35.334
I finally got
the coffee order right!

00:35.336 --> 00:37.503
Ohh!
<i>So there's nothing</i>
<i>more exciting</i>

00:37.505 --> 00:38.904
<i>than realizing your son</i>

00:38.906 --> 00:41.306
<i>might be more like you</i>
<i>than you thought</i>

00:41.308 --> 00:44.076
<i>and that he might have a shot</i>
<i>at a social life</i>

00:44.078 --> 00:46.645
<i>that doesn't involve</i>
<i>action figures and wizards.</i>

00:46.647 --> 00:47.813
Dre:
Hey, son.

00:47.815 --> 00:49.848
What's up?
Can I talk to you
for a second?

00:49.850 --> 00:51.083
Oh. Yeah.

00:51.085 --> 00:55.487
Um, are these kids here
to copy your homework?

00:55.489 --> 00:57.623
No.
They're my friends.

01:00.528 --> 01:03.262
Okay, go, go, go, go.
Go play with your friends.

01:07.868 --> 01:09.034
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

01:09.036 --> 01:10.669
Babe, babe, you'll never guess
what happened.

01:10.671 --> 01:11.703
Huh?

01:11.705 --> 01:13.005
Junior is over there
with his friends,

01:13.007 --> 01:15.107
and they are talking about
the Drake-Meek Mill beef, right?

01:15.109 --> 01:17.509
He said that Drake
"bodied" Meek.

01:17.511 --> 01:19.211
And I said,
"Son, is that good?"

01:19.213 --> 01:20.879
and he looked at me
and laughed.

01:20.881 --> 01:22.414
Okay?

01:22.416 --> 01:23.849
He sonned me, Bow.

01:23.851 --> 01:25.384
He said<i> I'm</i> the guy

01:25.386 --> 01:28.554
that's probably still listening
to Meek Mill.

01:28.556 --> 01:29.688
<i>He</i> bodied<i> me.</i>

01:29.690 --> 01:31.390
That means he destroyed me.

01:31.392 --> 01:33.058
That is very disrespectful.

01:33.060 --> 01:34.126
I should talk to him.

01:34.128 --> 01:35.594
Oh, yeah.
Try it.
Okay.

01:35.596 --> 01:37.062
He'll son you, too.
What?

01:37.064 --> 01:38.597
And I have never been prouder.

01:38.599 --> 01:39.598
[ Laughs ]

01:39.600 --> 01:41.700
Those guys he's with...

01:41.702 --> 01:43.569
[ Sighs ]
...they say
they're his friends,

01:43.571 --> 01:45.904
but I think they're probably
trying to get to me.

01:45.906 --> 01:48.574
Okay, Dre, Junior's been
hanging out with Wes and Kevin

01:48.576 --> 01:50.042
for the last couple of weeks.

01:50.044 --> 01:51.076
They're clicking.

01:51.078 --> 01:53.812
Uh, please, Bow,
they are not clicking.

01:53.814 --> 01:55.581
Okay.
All right?

01:55.583 --> 01:58.884
They are vibing
and on their way to a lituation.

01:58.886 --> 02:00.419
And if you were cool,

02:00.421 --> 02:03.422
you would know that
that is a lit situation.

02:03.424 --> 02:05.424
Did you just
look that up, Dre?
Nope.

02:05.426 --> 02:06.925
Give me your phone.

02:06.927 --> 02:08.160
It's, uh...
It's out of battery power.

02:08.162 --> 02:09.761
Mm-hmm.
Mm-hmm.

02:09.763 --> 02:11.230
[ Cellphone rings ]

02:11.232 --> 02:12.831
That's my, uh...

02:12.833 --> 02:15.767
That's my
out-of-battery-power ring.

02:15.769 --> 02:17.169
Okay.
It's just
letting me know

02:17.171 --> 02:19.138
that we can't
do nothing with it no more.
Right.

02:19.140 --> 02:21.273
Dre, I don't know
what the big deal is.

02:21.275 --> 02:23.008
Junior has always had friends.

02:23.010 --> 02:25.077
Yeah, but not like these.

02:25.079 --> 02:26.078
What?

02:26.080 --> 02:27.913
This is a game changer.

02:27.915 --> 02:29.148
What?
Bow...

02:29.150 --> 02:31.583
Huh?
I think I love him now.

02:31.585 --> 02:33.085
What? Dre...
I really feel it...

02:33.087 --> 02:35.687
Hey, Mom, can my boys
come over tomorrow?

02:35.689 --> 02:37.189
Oh, no, sweetheart.
Yes!

02:37.191 --> 02:38.624
We've got the...
Yes, son!

02:38.626 --> 02:40.993
We have...
Your boys
<i>can</i> come over tomorrow!

02:40.995 --> 02:43.629
Can I also get the new Jordans
coming out this Saturday?

02:43.631 --> 02:45.464
Maybe for
your birthday.
Quiet, woman!

02:45.466 --> 02:46.431
What the...?

02:48.102 --> 02:49.434
Yes.
Rainbow: Uh...

02:49.436 --> 02:52.538
Yes, you can get the new Jordans
coming out on Saturday, son.

02:52.540 --> 02:54.273
Oh, my God.

02:54.275 --> 02:56.275
[ Voice breaking ] This...

02:56.277 --> 02:59.278
is gonna be your first pair
of real kicks.

02:59.280 --> 03:01.547
Uh...
Dad,
are you crying?

03:01.549 --> 03:03.115
No!

03:03.117 --> 03:04.616
Okay, okay, okay.

03:04.618 --> 03:06.685
Junior, I love you!
Oh, my God.

03:06.687 --> 03:09.621
[ Crying ]

03:10.858 --> 03:13.559
Kids, come on!

03:13.561 --> 03:15.127
Who broke this?!

03:15.129 --> 03:16.728
[ Chuckles ]

03:16.730 --> 03:19.331
Ohh! Ohh!
My ankle!

03:19.333 --> 03:21.200
What got in your way,
the floor?

03:21.202 --> 03:23.202
[ Laughs ] You're in pain.

03:23.204 --> 03:25.337
It really hurts.
Are you okay?

03:25.339 --> 03:26.905
I'm okay,
it's just...
Okay, great.

03:26.907 --> 03:28.407
Come on.
Who broke this?!

03:28.409 --> 03:29.575
It wasn't me.

03:29.577 --> 03:30.676
Me, neither.

03:30.678 --> 03:32.010
Don't look at me.

03:32.012 --> 03:33.979
[ Grunts ] Ruby?

03:33.981 --> 03:35.214
Hmm? Yeah?

03:35.216 --> 03:39.051
Oh, are you asking
so you'll know who to thank?

03:39.053 --> 03:40.986
No...
It's hideous glassware.

03:40.988 --> 03:42.921
[ Scoffs ] It's just hideous.

03:42.923 --> 03:44.590
[ Sighs ] Hmph.

03:44.592 --> 03:45.591
What?

03:45.593 --> 03:48.427
What... What are you
hmph-ing about?

03:48.429 --> 03:49.895
Oh, no,
I'm... I'm sorry.

03:49.897 --> 03:50.929
I'm not judging.

03:50.931 --> 03:52.931
I-I just don't have
good "hmph" control.

03:52.933 --> 03:55.534
No, tell me.
I-I-I want to know.

03:55.536 --> 03:57.736
Well, I know I've only
been working here a few months.

03:57.738 --> 03:59.071
It's just...
It seems to me

03:59.073 --> 04:01.006
that a lot of things
get broken around here,

04:01.008 --> 04:04.509
and nobody seems to know
who did it or how.

04:04.511 --> 04:06.245
Oh.
♪ But she caught me
on the counter ♪

04:06.247 --> 04:07.346
[ Glass breaks ]

04:07.348 --> 04:08.347
♪ Wasn't me ♪

04:08.349 --> 04:09.514
♪ Saw me bangin' on the sofa ♪

04:09.516 --> 04:10.749
It wasn't me!
It wasn't me!

04:10.751 --> 04:12.017
♪ I even had her in the shower ♪

04:12.019 --> 04:13.051
It wasn't me.
It wasn't me. It wasn't me.

04:13.053 --> 04:14.253
♪ She even caught me on camera ♪

04:14.255 --> 04:15.754
[ Screams ] ♪ Wasn't me ♪

04:15.756 --> 04:17.723
♪ Saw the marks on my shoulder ♪
Let me guess.

04:17.725 --> 04:18.957
♪ Wasn't me ♪ It wasn't you.

04:20.427 --> 04:24.062
Well, Vivian, kids are
supposed to lie a<i> little.</i>

04:24.064 --> 04:25.197
Hmph!

04:25.199 --> 04:27.733
I'm sorry.
I-I did it again.

04:27.735 --> 04:31.069
It's just my mama used to always
say if you lie, you steal.

04:31.071 --> 04:32.571
If you steal, you kill.

04:32.573 --> 04:34.306
Yeah, well,
moms don't know everything.

04:34.308 --> 04:37.576
Well, none of my mom's kids
ever killed anybody...

04:37.578 --> 04:38.777
except Thelonious.

04:38.779 --> 04:40.045
What?
Mm...

04:40.047 --> 04:43.148
I just know I wouldn't let
my kids do me like that.

04:43.150 --> 04:44.650
But you know what?
It's not my house.

04:44.652 --> 04:45.751
[ Sighs ]

04:45.753 --> 04:47.252
[ Chuckles ] Uh, uh...

04:47.254 --> 04:48.320
Uh...

04:48.322 --> 04:50.155
Yeah, well... I...
are you gonna...?

04:50.157 --> 04:51.323
Hmm.

04:51.325 --> 04:54.559
Oh, look at this!
The boys are back.

04:54.561 --> 04:56.561
The crew.
The posse.

04:56.563 --> 04:58.664
The wolves.
The homies.

04:58.666 --> 05:00.632
♪ SquadGoals.

05:00.634 --> 05:03.435
Dad, you're giving us
douche chills.

05:03.437 --> 05:04.770
Oh, still sonning me.

05:04.772 --> 05:05.771
[ Chuckles ]

05:05.773 --> 05:09.107
What the hell happened
to your shoes?

05:09.109 --> 05:10.609
We were playing basketball.

05:10.611 --> 05:14.279
But... Boy, you<i> never</i> play
basketball in basketball shoes!

05:14.281 --> 05:16.982
You wear them to weddings,
funerals, and the Grammys.

05:16.984 --> 05:19.084
Then you dust them off
and resell them on eBay

05:19.086 --> 05:20.118
and get you some more.

05:20.120 --> 05:21.586
It's the circle of life, son!

05:21.588 --> 05:23.288
[ Laughter ] Your dad's funny.

05:23.290 --> 05:25.090
I got to go.
Yeah, me, too.

05:25.092 --> 05:27.259
I've got the Obama fundraiser.

05:27.261 --> 05:29.161
Another place
you could have worn your shoes.

05:29.163 --> 05:31.330
Hey, uh, Wes, how is it

05:31.332 --> 05:33.432
that you're able to go
to the Obama fundraiser?

05:33.434 --> 05:34.800
He kind of has to.

05:34.802 --> 05:36.134
It's at his house.

05:36.136 --> 05:38.170
Yeah, Obama's coming over early
to shower.

05:38.172 --> 05:41.773
Obama's...
showering at your house?

05:41.775 --> 05:43.275
Well, the<i> Malibu</i> house.

05:43.277 --> 05:45.110
How... How... How many houses
do you guys have?

05:45.112 --> 05:46.611
Me personally or my parents?

05:46.613 --> 05:47.846
Well, you know.

05:47.848 --> 05:49.781
'Cause I just have
the one in Brentwood.
Uh...

05:49.783 --> 05:52.451
I haven't asked my parents
how many houses they have.

05:52.453 --> 05:54.152
That would be gauche.

05:54.154 --> 05:56.054
Ah, it's... it's...

05:56.056 --> 05:59.391
I...

05:59.393 --> 06:00.492
"Gauche."

06:00.494 --> 06:02.361
Borrowed from the French
<i>"gauchir,"</i>

06:02.363 --> 06:04.730
meaning
to be socially awkward, clumsy.

06:04.732 --> 06:07.332
Used in a sentence...
"When Dre doesn't want

06:07.334 --> 06:09.301
to make eye contact with me
at the urinal,

06:09.303 --> 06:10.736
that is gauche."

06:10.738 --> 06:13.071
Who talks like that?
Hmm?

06:13.073 --> 06:16.675
Dre:
Can you believe these rich brats
with their Obama fundraisers?

06:16.677 --> 06:18.577
Dre, Junior is gonna be fine,
okay?

06:18.579 --> 06:21.713
It's... It's good that he's
hanging out with wealthy people.

06:21.715 --> 06:23.515
Wealthy people are superior.

06:23.517 --> 06:26.017
Yeah.
They're worth more.
Wealthy lives matter,
Dre.

06:26.019 --> 06:27.386
What?

06:27.388 --> 06:28.720
Uh, oh, okay,
that came out wrong.

06:28.722 --> 06:32.524
Uh, wealthy lives matter most.

06:32.526 --> 06:34.559
There we go.
Yeah,
that's what I meant.

06:34.561 --> 06:36.428
See,<i> that</i> is
what I'm worried about.

06:36.430 --> 06:39.765
I don't want Junior
to lose touch with reality.

06:39.767 --> 06:41.400
Th-That is ridiculous.

06:41.402 --> 06:43.001
Do I seem out of touch to you?

06:43.003 --> 06:44.002
Hmm?
Okay.

06:44.004 --> 06:45.737
How much
does a loaf of bread cost?

06:45.739 --> 06:47.672
$195.

06:47.674 --> 06:49.074
Josh:
Boom. Nailed it.

06:49.076 --> 06:51.042
You are
completely out of touch.

06:51.044 --> 06:53.245
Okay, all right.
So I don't do my own shopping.

06:53.247 --> 06:54.780
I'm not a woman.
[ Chuckles ]

06:54.782 --> 06:56.381
Honestly,
Dre-Doggy-Dawg,

06:56.383 --> 06:59.418
Junior hanging out with rich
folks can only be a good thing.

06:59.420 --> 07:00.719
Hmm.

07:00.721 --> 07:02.421
When I needed a kidney,
my parents' rich friends

07:02.423 --> 07:04.756
knew just the right
Indian village to go to

07:04.758 --> 07:06.124
to get me a new one.
Oh, yeah.

07:06.126 --> 07:08.059
Thank you, Sanjay.

07:08.061 --> 07:09.261
[ Clicks tongue ] Namaste.

07:09.263 --> 07:10.796
What you really need
to worry about

07:10.798 --> 07:12.431
is rich people's
best-kept secret.

07:15.102 --> 07:18.570
They like to keep minorities
as pets.

07:18.572 --> 07:19.604
Hey.

07:19.606 --> 07:22.808
Did you see the documentary
"The Toy"?

07:22.810 --> 07:23.942
Hmm?

07:23.944 --> 07:25.143
Charlie...

07:25.145 --> 07:28.580
that was a scripted film
starring Richard Pryor.

07:28.582 --> 07:30.782
Was it, Dre?
Was it?

07:30.784 --> 07:33.952
Yes, Charlie!
It was! Yes, it was!

07:33.954 --> 07:36.955
The flesh wants everything
but wisdom, don't it?

07:36.957 --> 07:38.290
Uh...
Wisdom.

07:38.292 --> 07:40.125
Dre, you know what?

07:40.127 --> 07:41.259
My God.

07:41.261 --> 07:43.094
Stevens: Your son
is going to be fine, okay?

07:43.096 --> 07:46.832
Now, seriously, how close was I
to the cost of that bread, huh?

07:46.834 --> 07:50.569
Was I high or low
or... what?

07:50.571 --> 07:56.775
So, obviously, this anonymous
confession box didn't work.

07:56.777 --> 07:59.744
But I still need my confession.

07:59.746 --> 08:02.080
Okay, I'll go first.

08:02.082 --> 08:04.249
I've broken things.
Mm-hmm.

08:04.251 --> 08:05.484
I've lied.

08:05.486 --> 08:06.818
I've lied to your father.

08:06.820 --> 08:07.953
[ Scoffs ]

08:07.955 --> 08:09.788
Lied about
some very important things

08:09.790 --> 08:11.189
for a good reason

08:11.191 --> 08:12.924
because your father is not
very good at handling things,

08:12.926 --> 08:14.326
but he forgave me,

08:14.328 --> 08:19.831
and I will forgive you
as soon as I know who...

08:20.601 --> 08:22.634
to forgive.

08:22.636 --> 08:24.035
It wasn't me.
It wasn't me. It wasn't me.

08:24.037 --> 08:25.170
Come on.

08:25.172 --> 08:27.539
Listen, uh, Rainbow, Rainbow,
honey, let it go.

08:27.541 --> 08:29.341
Somebody did you a favor.

08:29.343 --> 08:32.177
Choosing dinnerware
is not your strong suit.

08:32.179 --> 08:34.346
You know,
like cooking or cleaning

08:34.348 --> 08:36.114
or wearing
age-appropriate clothing.

08:36.116 --> 08:37.449
Come on.
I think...

08:37.451 --> 08:38.550
[ Mutters ]

08:38.552 --> 08:39.651
Can we go now?

08:39.653 --> 08:40.886
No.

08:40.888 --> 08:43.321
Thelonious used to talk to Mama
just like that.

08:43.323 --> 08:47.392
Now he talks to her on a phone
through Plexiglas, okay?

08:47.394 --> 08:48.860
But it's
none of my business.
Mnh-mnh.

08:48.862 --> 08:50.795
Uh, who is that?

08:50.797 --> 08:52.898
Come on, guys.

08:52.900 --> 08:54.232
I didn't do it.

08:54.234 --> 08:55.400
Me, neither.

08:55.402 --> 08:56.701
It wasn't me.

08:56.703 --> 08:58.069
That's it!

08:58.071 --> 09:00.171
You're grounded!

09:00.173 --> 09:01.907
No Kanye concert for you.

09:01.909 --> 09:03.742
Jack, no basketball for you.

09:03.744 --> 09:05.410
No alcohol for you.

09:05.412 --> 09:06.845
And...

09:06.847 --> 09:07.846
Oh, my God.

09:07.848 --> 09:09.915
Is there anything
that you love?

09:09.917 --> 09:12.517
Revenge.
No vengeance
for you.

09:12.519 --> 09:13.752
Get out!

09:13.754 --> 09:14.853
Ruby: Listen.
I don't...

09:14.855 --> 09:16.254
It's not...
[ Shouts indistinctly ]

09:16.256 --> 09:18.256
I'd say
I was gonna get you for this,

09:18.258 --> 09:20.025
but I guess
that's off the table.

09:20.027 --> 09:22.561
Keep walking.

09:22.563 --> 09:23.728
Ow!

09:23.730 --> 09:26.698
Stevens doesn't even know
the cost of bread, Bow!

09:26.700 --> 09:28.099
Why are we talking about bread?

09:28.101 --> 09:29.267
Because God only knows

09:29.269 --> 09:31.002
the kind people
that Junior hanging out with.

09:31.004 --> 09:33.738
Who invites a 14-year-old
to fly on their private jet

09:33.740 --> 09:35.574
to see a Warriors playoff game?

09:35.576 --> 09:36.875
They did that?
Yes!

09:36.877 --> 09:38.376
They're monsters.
Right?

09:38.378 --> 09:42.013
Uh, Dre, if you're so worried
about who these people are,

09:42.015 --> 09:43.515
then why don't you just
go meet them?

09:43.517 --> 09:44.883
You're right.
Mm-hmm.

09:44.885 --> 09:46.351
Junior's going over
to Wes' house

09:46.353 --> 09:47.619
for a sleep-over
tomorrow night.

09:47.621 --> 09:48.853
I will introduce myself then.

09:48.855 --> 09:51.022
I'll play it cool.
[ Gasps ]

09:51.024 --> 09:53.391
I'll wear all my jewelry.

09:53.393 --> 09:55.860
Do you want
my ring?
Unh-unh.
That's too much.

09:55.862 --> 09:58.029
But have you seen
my grill, though?

09:58.031 --> 09:59.731
N-No.
Damn it.

09:59.733 --> 10:01.700
I threw it away, Dre.

10:01.702 --> 10:04.035
Why would you
do that?
Oh, my God.

10:07.708 --> 10:08.807
Welcome.
Wow!

10:08.809 --> 10:10.575
This is an amazing view.

10:10.577 --> 10:11.643
Oh, thank you.

10:11.645 --> 10:13.311
That's exactly what Obama said.

10:13.313 --> 10:16.748
Of course, he was trying to get
me to write huge check, so...

10:16.750 --> 10:17.916
[ Chuckling ] Barry.

10:17.918 --> 10:20.418
Yo, you want to go watch
the next "Lego Movie"?

10:20.420 --> 10:21.419
'Cause we have it.
Oh.

10:21.421 --> 10:23.288
Wes: Yeah?
The next "Lego Movie"?

10:23.290 --> 10:24.723
It isn't even out yet.

10:24.725 --> 10:26.424
Hell, does Warner Bros.
Even have it?

10:26.426 --> 10:27.759
[ Scoffs ]

10:27.761 --> 10:29.594
And how can you see a movie
in here with all this sunlight?

10:29.596 --> 10:30.629
Oh, no, no, no.

10:30.631 --> 10:32.097
We... We don't watch movies
in here.

10:32.099 --> 10:35.500
I mean, the sun puts on a show
for us every single day.

10:35.502 --> 10:38.236
But, no, we... we take the
elevator down to the movie room.

10:38.238 --> 10:40.271
Junior: Oh, uh, Dad,
we're heading downstairs,

10:40.273 --> 10:41.640
so don't worry about me.

10:41.642 --> 10:43.675
The driver's
bringing me home tomorrow.

10:43.677 --> 10:44.776
Okay.

10:44.778 --> 10:45.810
So you can go.

10:45.812 --> 10:47.846
All right,
the sooner the better.

10:47.848 --> 10:48.847
Cool.

10:48.849 --> 10:50.582
Is that a skull?

10:50.584 --> 10:52.484
Yeah. Sure is.

10:52.486 --> 10:55.920
Yeah, it used to hold the brains
of a saber-toothed tiger.

10:55.922 --> 10:57.922
Now it holds just some gum.

10:57.924 --> 10:59.090
Dre: Oh.

10:59.092 --> 11:00.992
Can I get you something to eat,
by the way?

11:00.994 --> 11:02.260
Sure.
What do you have?

11:02.262 --> 11:04.496
Well, touch of a button,
I can get you anything you want.

11:04.498 --> 11:05.630
Anything?

11:05.632 --> 11:06.765
Literally anything.

11:06.767 --> 11:09.267
So, what if, uh, I said,
like, a hamburger?

11:09.269 --> 11:10.935
Sure.
How would you like it cooked?
Oh, uh, mm...

11:10.937 --> 11:13.004
Mnh-mnh. Mnh-mnh.

11:13.006 --> 11:15.774
Chicago deep-dish pizza.

11:15.776 --> 11:17.008
South Side or North?

11:17.010 --> 11:19.110
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, okay, hold on.

11:19.112 --> 11:21.946
Wait a minute.
Let's make this count.

11:24.017 --> 11:27.018
Sushi-inspired
Thanksgiving dinner.

11:27.020 --> 11:28.720
Ah, I love that.

11:28.722 --> 11:29.988
We had that two nights ago.

11:29.990 --> 11:31.122
Uh...

11:31.124 --> 11:32.991
Want to take a seat
out on the veranda?

11:32.993 --> 11:34.059
Sure.
Okay.

11:34.061 --> 11:36.661
You'd have to take off
your shoes, please.

11:36.663 --> 11:38.797
To go outside?
Yeah.

11:38.799 --> 11:40.665
Okay, I'm not about
to miss this concert

11:40.667 --> 11:42.367
for something
that I didn't even do.

11:42.369 --> 11:44.402
Whoever broke that glass
needs to come clean.

11:44.404 --> 11:45.737
All right, listen, listen.

11:45.739 --> 11:47.405
I know exactly what to do.

11:47.407 --> 11:49.741
In the Bible, they're always
dealing with this kind of crap.

11:49.743 --> 11:52.177
Huh?
What we need
is a sacrificial lamb.

11:52.179 --> 11:53.311
Jack: No!

11:53.313 --> 11:56.081
We need to stick together.

11:56.083 --> 11:57.482
Ride or die!

11:57.484 --> 11:58.850
All for one!

11:58.852 --> 12:01.019
Don't let them
get into our heads, okay?

12:01.021 --> 12:02.153
We can do this!

12:02.155 --> 12:03.755
Jack did it.
He told us.

12:03.757 --> 12:05.156
Smashed it right up.

12:05.158 --> 12:06.991
Mm-hmm.
Saw it with my own eyes.

12:06.993 --> 12:08.359
Diane: Yeah.
Oh, yeah.

12:08.361 --> 12:11.062
Must be cool to have
your own private beach, huh?

12:11.064 --> 12:13.164
Oh, yeah.
Well, not exactly private.

12:13.166 --> 12:15.867
Spielberg's dog Jaws
thinks he owns the place.

12:15.869 --> 12:17.569
Oh. [ Chuckles ]
Well...

12:19.673 --> 12:23.842
Ah, I can't believe I'm hitting
golf balls into the ocean.

12:23.844 --> 12:26.044
I think you're about 100 yards
short, but I get the idea.

12:26.046 --> 12:27.746
Sorry, Steven.

12:27.748 --> 12:29.781
Oh. My bad, S.S.!

12:29.783 --> 12:31.249
That's not...
No?

12:31.251 --> 12:33.384
That's not appropriate.
Okay.

12:33.386 --> 12:34.853
He doesn't...
He doesn't prefer that.

12:34.855 --> 12:35.954
Ahh.

12:35.956 --> 12:38.556
So, does, uh...
Now, does Junior play golf?

12:38.558 --> 12:40.024
Wes and I hit up Pebble.

12:40.026 --> 12:43.194
You know, maybe the four of us
could chopper up there sometime.

12:43.196 --> 12:44.295
Ah, chopper to Pebble.

12:44.297 --> 12:45.530
Yeah.

12:45.532 --> 12:46.865
Those words have
come out of my mouth before now.

12:46.867 --> 12:47.899
[ Chuckles ]

12:47.901 --> 12:49.434
Well, if... if golf's
not your thing,

12:49.436 --> 12:51.136
what... what do you and Junior
like to do?

12:51.138 --> 12:52.270
Together?

12:52.272 --> 12:54.305
We play video games.

12:54.307 --> 12:55.573
Wes loves video games.

12:55.575 --> 12:56.641
Oh.

12:56.643 --> 12:58.043
Now, I set him up
with an internship

12:58.044 --> 12:59.544
at Riot Games in Tokyo.

12:59.546 --> 13:01.746
Oh. Really?

13:01.748 --> 13:03.114
Now he's fluent in Japanese.

13:03.116 --> 13:04.382
Wow.
Yeah.

13:04.384 --> 13:05.784
Nice!
Mm-hmm.

13:05.786 --> 13:07.418
Well, Junior's looking to intern
this summer, too.

13:07.420 --> 13:08.419
Oh, that's great.
Mm-hmm.

13:08.421 --> 13:09.420
Where?

13:09.422 --> 13:10.822
Uh...

13:10.824 --> 13:13.892
Uh, he has lots of options.

13:13.894 --> 13:16.494
Uh, th-the U.N.
Great.

13:16.496 --> 13:18.396
And there's NASA.

13:18.398 --> 13:19.597
Fantastic.

13:19.599 --> 13:20.932
You know, but he really
doesn't have the time

13:20.934 --> 13:22.500
because he's so busy
playing polo.

13:22.502 --> 13:23.601
Oh, fantastic.

13:23.603 --> 13:24.602
What club do you belong to?

13:24.604 --> 13:27.272
Uh... Marco Polo.

13:27.274 --> 13:32.177
It... It... It's a...
It's a black-only polo club.

13:32.179 --> 13:33.678
See, my... my...
my grandparents...

13:33.680 --> 13:38.783
They... They founded the first
black bank back in, ooh, 1979?

13:38.785 --> 13:42.153
You know,
it's called Johnson Mutual.

13:42.155 --> 13:43.588
You know, we had Ben Vereen

13:43.590 --> 13:47.091
and... and... and
Scatman Crothers
as our ambassadors.

13:47.093 --> 13:49.794
Yeah, yeah,
we have old black money.

13:49.796 --> 13:51.596
Hmm.
Aunt Jemima
old black money.

13:51.598 --> 13:52.630
Okay.
It's dusty.

13:52.632 --> 13:53.865
Right.
Yeah, you know,

13:53.867 --> 13:55.200
but we don't really
talk about that.

13:55.202 --> 13:56.634
You know, that's, uh...
that's gauch-ay.

13:56.636 --> 13:57.635
[ Chuckles ]

13:57.637 --> 13:58.636
Right.
Yeah.

13:58.638 --> 13:59.804
Are you okay, Dre?

13:59.806 --> 14:00.805
Yes!

14:00.807 --> 14:02.440
Would you excuse me
for a second?

14:02.442 --> 14:03.474
Uh, be right back.

14:03.476 --> 14:05.176
Sure.

14:05.178 --> 14:07.011
Hey. Oh.

14:07.013 --> 14:08.546
Mystery solved.

14:08.548 --> 14:11.115
The girls told me Jack did it.

14:11.117 --> 14:14.285
Oh, and you're just gonna take
their word for it?

14:14.287 --> 14:16.221
[ Scoffs ]

14:16.223 --> 14:17.288
No!

14:17.290 --> 14:18.623
Oh.

14:18.625 --> 14:22.527
I'm obviously gonna talk to Jack
to make sure that he did it,

14:22.529 --> 14:25.830
which he did,
because my kids don't lie.

14:25.832 --> 14:27.198
Mm-hmm.

14:27.200 --> 14:30.401
I mean, except for in
this instance, w-which he did.

14:30.403 --> 14:33.171
But he's...
He's about to tell me the truth.

14:33.173 --> 14:34.305
[ Chuckles ]

14:34.307 --> 14:35.573
Hmph!

14:35.575 --> 14:37.575
[ Chuckles ]

14:37.577 --> 14:39.544
Hmm....

14:39.546 --> 14:41.846
Ooh! Ooh!
Oh, hey.

14:41.848 --> 14:43.147
Where's your sink?

14:43.149 --> 14:45.083
Oh, yeah, it's right down
the hallway in the bathroom.

14:45.085 --> 14:46.184
What did you think

14:46.186 --> 14:49.454
of my Moroccan humidor
back there, huh?

14:51.992 --> 14:53.258
Why do we have to leave?

14:53.260 --> 14:55.326
We were halfway through
the new "Lego Movie."

14:55.328 --> 14:56.895
Because everything
is not awesome, all right?

14:56.897 --> 14:58.029
We had to get up out of there.

14:58.031 --> 14:59.497
Those people are bad...
liars.

14:59.499 --> 15:01.266
And they're probably
gonna lie to you

15:01.268 --> 15:03.334
about an innocent mistake
that I didn't make.

15:03.336 --> 15:04.869
Dad,
what are you talking about?

15:04.871 --> 15:06.905
They are bad people
with bad values

15:06.907 --> 15:08.873
and misleading
porcelain chairs.

15:08.875 --> 15:11.676
For God's sake, who would leave
magazines right next to it?!

15:11.678 --> 15:13.177
Did you use the bathroom in...

15:13.179 --> 15:14.412
You have changed!

15:14.414 --> 15:17.749
Because the old Junior
would not accuse me of that.

15:17.751 --> 15:18.750
[ Engine starts ]

15:18.752 --> 15:20.685
They were gonna keep you
as a pet, son.

15:20.687 --> 15:22.287
Didn't you see "The Toy"?

15:22.289 --> 15:23.421
I saved your life.

15:23.423 --> 15:24.689
[ Tires squeal ]

15:28.428 --> 15:29.594
[ Door opens ] Hey.

15:29.596 --> 15:30.762
What are you doing home?

15:30.764 --> 15:32.397
I hate Dad!
[ Door closes ]

15:32.399 --> 15:34.365
Well, that I can understand.

15:34.367 --> 15:36.067
What happened, Dre?

15:36.069 --> 15:40.071
He is embarrassed by his father
for no apparent reason.

15:40.073 --> 15:41.072
Hmm.

15:41.074 --> 15:42.807
No reason.

15:42.809 --> 15:43.975
Well...

15:43.977 --> 15:45.977
[ Violin playing ]

15:51.384 --> 15:54.552
[ Laughing ] Oh, my God.

15:54.554 --> 15:56.921
[ Snorts ] Oh.

15:56.923 --> 15:59.424
Okay, Dre, how could you
possibly mistake that for...

15:59.426 --> 16:01.259
Look, you weren't there,
okay?
[ Groans ]

16:01.261 --> 16:03.328
Well, now you're gonna have to
kill yourself.

16:04.297 --> 16:06.798
I should have never let him
hang with those kids.

16:06.800 --> 16:08.766
What does that have to do
with anything?

16:08.768 --> 16:11.602
Because now that he's
seen that world, he's gonna
be embarrassed by me.

16:11.604 --> 16:15.506
Look, when I was 15,

16:15.508 --> 16:17.909
I walked this girl,
Valerie Emmett, home.

16:17.911 --> 16:19.243
Her family was rich,

16:19.245 --> 16:22.814
and they had this fancy house
in this fancy neighborhood.

16:22.816 --> 16:27.485
Her mother opened the door in
a Chanel suit, wearing pearls.

16:27.487 --> 16:28.987
My first thought was,

16:28.989 --> 16:31.622
"I can never show her
where I live."

16:31.624 --> 16:32.824
[ Siren wailing, dog barking ]
♪ Straight outta Compton ♪

16:32.826 --> 16:34.659
♪ There's a crazy brother
named Ice Cube ♪

16:34.661 --> 16:37.095
♪ From the super-dope gang
with an attitude ♪

16:37.097 --> 16:39.764
I suddenly became embarrassed
by where I was from.

16:39.766 --> 16:43.668
Dre, your mother's
fashion choices, beliefs,

16:43.670 --> 16:45.837
and personality aside...

16:45.839 --> 16:48.973
you had nothing
to be ashamed of.

16:48.975 --> 16:50.675
Plus,
we put Junior in that school

16:50.677 --> 16:53.177
so that he could see a lot
of different points of view.

16:53.179 --> 16:56.214
It doesn't mean
he's gonna lose his own.

16:56.216 --> 16:57.315
You're right.

16:57.317 --> 16:59.150
But how's he gonna admire me?

16:59.152 --> 17:02.186
I don't have anything
prehistoric to put my gum in.

17:02.188 --> 17:03.388
You will one day.

17:04.691 --> 17:05.857
Okay.

17:05.859 --> 17:08.026
[ Indistinct conversation,
Jack grunting ]

17:08.028 --> 17:11.696
Mom's got you doing trash
as punishment?

17:11.698 --> 17:14.565
Yeah.
It's so heavy.

17:14.567 --> 17:16.667
Well,
sucks for you, homey.
Dude.

17:16.669 --> 17:19.037
Yeah, it does suck
because I didn't even do it.

17:19.039 --> 17:20.838
Then, wait...
why'd you say you did?

17:20.840 --> 17:23.241
I didn't want you to miss out
on the Kanye concert,

17:23.243 --> 17:25.376
and didn't want you to miss out
on revenge.

17:25.378 --> 17:28.312
I thought if I confessed,
Mom would forgive me.

17:28.314 --> 17:31.082
I guess I'm just dumb.

17:31.084 --> 17:33.551
Dumb, clumsy Jack.

17:33.553 --> 17:34.852
Mm-hmm.

17:34.854 --> 17:38.189
You know what?
Let us help you.

17:38.191 --> 17:39.857
You need to go rest your leg.

17:39.859 --> 17:40.992
Really?

17:40.994 --> 17:42.160
Mm-hmm.

17:42.162 --> 17:43.261
I guess so.

17:43.263 --> 17:45.063
Thank you, guys.

17:45.065 --> 17:46.397
You're the best.

17:46.399 --> 17:48.199
Careful with that one.

17:48.201 --> 17:50.068
It's full of fish guts.

17:50.070 --> 17:51.602
See, look at that.

17:51.604 --> 17:54.372
See how they're helping
their brother?

17:54.374 --> 17:56.507
You know,
maybe I don't do it like you,

17:56.509 --> 17:58.843
but what do I know?

17:58.845 --> 18:04.282
I'm just a mother of four kind,
trustworthy, honest kids.

18:04.284 --> 18:07.251
If he's so honest, then why...

18:07.253 --> 18:08.886
Why is he not limping anymore?

18:08.888 --> 18:11.255
[ Clicks tongue ]
Let me break it down for you.

18:11.257 --> 18:13.224
First...

18:13.226 --> 18:15.259
♪♪

18:15.261 --> 18:17.061
He broke the glass.

18:17.063 --> 18:18.262
♪♪

18:18.264 --> 18:19.931
Then...

18:19.933 --> 18:21.099
Kids!

18:21.101 --> 18:22.200
Who broke this?!

18:22.202 --> 18:24.969
He had to paint himself
as sympathetic.

18:24.971 --> 18:26.070
Ohh!

18:26.072 --> 18:28.072
Ohh!
My ankle!

18:28.074 --> 18:29.407
Ohh!
Diane:
Jack did it.

18:29.409 --> 18:30.408
Zoey:
He told us.

18:30.410 --> 18:31.642
Smashed it right up.

18:31.644 --> 18:33.411
Rainbow:
Then he found out

18:33.413 --> 18:35.646
his partners
threw him under the bus.

18:35.648 --> 18:37.648
So he made a plan to confess.

18:37.650 --> 18:39.150
I knocked it off the cabinet?

18:39.152 --> 18:40.651
You're doing the right thing.

18:40.653 --> 18:45.923
But then he filled up trash bags
with fish guts to make them pay.

18:45.925 --> 18:48.759
Oh!
[ Indistinct conversation ]

18:48.761 --> 18:51.762
And he thought
he got away with it.

18:51.764 --> 18:53.064
♪♪

18:53.066 --> 18:54.499
If you knew the whole time,

18:54.501 --> 18:56.934
then why didn't you just
crack his ass the old way?

18:56.936 --> 18:58.803
Well, I had a hunch,
but I couldn't prove it.

18:58.805 --> 19:01.038
I mean, if I investigated
every cold case around here,

19:01.040 --> 19:02.573
I'd never get to enjoy my kids.

19:02.575 --> 19:06.978
So can we have a little less
"Hmph!" and a lot more "Huh!"?

19:06.980 --> 19:08.079
I'll try.

19:08.081 --> 19:09.280
Okay.

19:09.282 --> 19:10.748
I can't make any promises
about my side-eye.

19:10.750 --> 19:12.016
No, no, no.

19:12.018 --> 19:13.084
Ohh! Ohh!

19:13.086 --> 19:14.352
I...

19:14.354 --> 19:15.586
It wasn't me!

19:15.588 --> 19:16.821
You're grounded!

19:18.291 --> 19:20.424
Aah!
My plantar fasciitis!

19:20.426 --> 19:21.592
Aah! Aah! Aah!

19:21.594 --> 19:24.862
[ Groaning ]

19:24.864 --> 19:26.764
Help!

19:26.766 --> 19:28.699
[ Chuckles ]

19:28.701 --> 19:29.767
Hey.

19:29.769 --> 19:30.768
Hey.

19:30.770 --> 19:32.370
[ Sighs ]

19:32.372 --> 19:36.140
Oh, Dad,
that's a chair and only a chair.

19:36.142 --> 19:38.776
Look, I'm sorry I yanked you
out of that house, son.

19:38.778 --> 19:40.878
But look, the thing is,

19:40.880 --> 19:44.382
there are gonna be people
who have more than you.

19:44.384 --> 19:47.685
But the trick is
to not get freaked out by it.

19:47.687 --> 19:51.322
Are you talking to me
or talking to yourself?

19:51.324 --> 19:52.957
[ Sighs ]

19:52.959 --> 19:55.393
Myself, I guess.

19:55.395 --> 19:59.297
You are my son,
so I assume you're just like me,

19:59.299 --> 20:01.799
except you're a lot smarter
than I am.

20:01.801 --> 20:04.135
And a lot less insecure.
Uh...

20:04.137 --> 20:06.170
And I can tell what's a chair
and what's a toilet.

20:06.172 --> 20:08.072
Okay, look, son...
[ Sighs ]

20:08.074 --> 20:12.376
I don't ever want you to feel
that I'm not enough for you.

20:12.378 --> 20:15.246
Dad, don't worry.

20:15.248 --> 20:17.315
You're enough.

20:17.317 --> 20:18.416
Mm.

20:18.418 --> 20:21.052
And if I'm being honest,
probably too much.

20:21.054 --> 20:23.421
Mom and I talk about it a lot.

20:23.423 --> 20:25.756
[ Sighs ]
Sometimes,
it's all we talk about.

20:25.758 --> 20:27.592
I am a lot.

20:27.594 --> 20:29.160
You are.

20:30.163 --> 20:35.533
We can never go back there,
you know?

20:35.535 --> 20:37.668
I know.

20:37.670 --> 20:39.937
I know.

20:41.174 --> 20:42.373
Ohh.

20:42.375 --> 20:43.574
My bad.

20:43.576 --> 20:44.675
Yeah.

20:48.948 --> 20:49.947
Anything you want for breakfast,
you can have.

20:49.949 --> 20:51.282
Anything?
Anything.

20:51.284 --> 20:55.086
Okay, uh, poached quail egg
with brioche and mango.

20:55.088 --> 20:56.754
Oh. Uh, uh, uh...
I would also like...

20:56.756 --> 20:58.956
I was kind of hoping
that you would say "cereal."

20:58.958 --> 21:00.424
Oh. Okay.
Mm-hmm.

21:00.426 --> 21:01.726
Uh, so, Apple Jacks.

21:01.728 --> 21:04.362
Or...? Rai-i-i-i-

21:04.364 --> 21:05.529
Raisin Bran.

21:05.531 --> 21:07.098
Ah!
Great!

21:07.100 --> 21:09.734
With milk.
Or...?

21:09.736 --> 21:12.870
So this really only works
if I said dry Raisin Bran.

21:12.872 --> 21:14.305
Ah! Excellent choice!
Hold on.

21:14.307 --> 21:15.740
Let me grab that for you.

21:15.742 --> 21:18.209
Just like at Wes' house.

21:19.712 --> 21:21.746
Hmm.

21:21.748 --> 21:23.347
[ Blows ]
